    "description": "Details A relaxed London book club exploring the most influential book in history. Whether you think it s rubbish, holy, or you re simply not sure what to make of it, you re very welcome. We meet for two hours at a time. Our reading list includes books from the Bible as well as some of the books that didn t make it into most Bibles. The Bible has shaped culture, law, art and ethics for centuries, yet many people are personally unfamiliar with it. Each evening is structured but informal. The group chooses the book or books to read, and discussion takes place in small groups. No lectures. No pressure. No need to prepare anything in advance. The aim is thoughtful, respectful conversation. Plenty of people feel they know quite a bit about the Bible, yet struggle to read it. This is a space to explore it thoughtfully and honestly in good company. This club is for: Curious thinkers Skeptics Christians with questions Anyone who wants to make up their own mind Our only rules?",
